# AXIS Decision Engine

Use the routing output to choose an execution strategy.

## Strategy Map

| Type     | Complexity | Strategy                                      |
|----------|------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| BUILD    | low        | Write directly, verify output                 |
| BUILD    | medium     | State plan first, execute step by step        |
| BUILD    | high       | Confirm scope with user before any writes     |
| FIX      | low        | Reproduce, patch, verify                      |
| FIX      | medium     | Isolate root cause, patch, regression check   |
| FIX      | high       | Confirm before touching shared/prod paths     |
| REFACTOR | any        | Show diff intent first, then apply            |
| EXPLAIN  | any        | Read code/files first, then respond           |
| CONFIG   | low        | Apply change, show result                     |
| CONFIG   | high       | Confirm before modifying shared config        |

## Output of this step

State the chosen strategy explicitly before moving to execution.mdc:

```
[DECISION] Strategy: <strategy summary in one line>
```
